Thanks Nate!

Nate Ledbetter <ltdomer98@...> wrote:

--- Rod Pavez <grfkboyz@...> wrote:

> Hey there everybody:
> Quick question about musuems in Japan. I don't know
> if this question
> qualifies but I was wondering if there are any
> museums in Japan that
> specialize in western culture dealing with art and
> so forth.
> I looked through the internet but came up dry. Just
> wondering if
> anybody knew.
> Thanks

Quite a few, actually. Plenty of modern art museums,
etc. Hakone has an open air sculpture museum, with
sections of Picasso. Yokohama has several, Tokyo also.

messages.msgSnippet: Thanks for the info. Michael! Michael Peters  wrote: Rod wrote  I was wondering if there are any museums in Japan that ... Yes there are
messages.messageBody:
Thanks for the info. Michael!


Michael Peters <shdwstel@...> wrote:
Rod wrote " I was wondering if there are any museums in Japan that
>specialize in western culture dealing with art and so forth."

Yes there are many. They have a museum of western art at Ueno as well as a
regular art museum that has many western items as well. If there is a
western art exhibition on tour, it almost certainly makes a stop in Tokyo.
